  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Secrets1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e0b2833548f8d5b2</T>
      <T n="text">0xD261FC2D<!--String: "When your Sim gets up to no good away from the public eye, it might create a scandalous <b><font color='#199C2C'>Secret</font></b> that can then be <b><font color='#199C2C'>Discovered</font></b> and exploited by other Sims. Likewise, your Sim can <b><font color='#199C2C'>Ask for Secrets</font></b> or even <b><font color='#199C2C'>Buy Secrets</font></b> about others, both of which offer up the option to make the secret real or dismiss it without consequences.\n\nOnce discovered, Secrets can be used to <b><font color='#199C2C'>Extort</font></b> other Sims to gain Simoleons, remove workplace rivals, influence Dynasty decisions or even meddle in Noble life. Sims can also choose to protect the Secret Holder's honor by becoming their <b><font color='#199C2C'>Confidante</font></b>."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Secrets2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e0b2833548f8d5b1</T>
      <T n="text">0x7E87987E<!--String: "The <b><font color='#199C2C'>Information Broker</font></b> is a reliable conduit for digging up, revealing or getting rid of pesky Secrets. They are willing to <b><font color='#199C2C'>Buy Secrets</font></b> but can also <b><font color='#199C2C'>Sell</font></b> them or <b><font color='#199C2C'>Bury</font></b> them for you so that they disappear completely. The fastest way to access the Information Broker is via Computer in the Scandals menu, or befriend Ondarion locals and ask them for secrets to try and discover the Information Broker's true identity.\n\nFeeling overwhelmed by all the tea? Use the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Notebook</font></b> to keep track of your own as well as other Sims' Secrets, and see how much longer they'll be a liability."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
